    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>coated cheese </strong>to a pot with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>and <strong>reserved starchy pasta water </strong>and bring to a boil over a medium heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 2-3 min, stirring frequently, or until the cheese has melted and thickened – this is your <strong>cheese sauce</strong></p>",
